article.headline: Vermont 48, Harvard 42
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Taylor Coppenrath scored 19 points as Vermont overcame a poor offensive effort to hold off Harvard, 48-42 on Sunday. Vermont's 48 points were the fewest in a victory since 1985 when they topped Colgate, 37-34 and it was the fewest points they allowed since topping Dartmouth, 62-41, in November of 2002. The Catamounts (2-4) shot only 30 percent from the floor and a woeful 1-for-14 from 3-point range while limiting Harvard to 27 percent from the field. Coppenrath hit 13-of-14 free throws as Vermont hit 19-of-27 from the line. Harvard had only 10 free throws and hit eight of them. Harvard took an 18-8 lead as Vermont hit only one of its first 16 shots. However, Coppenrath scored nine points as the Catamounts went on a 15-1 run and they led 23-22 at the half. Matt Stehle led Harvard with 13 points. Jason Norman and Kevin Rogus each had 10 points.
